cs.CR, cs.IT, cs.CY, cs.SY, cs.LG

The paper discusses a lightweight encryption algorithm for securing data in the Internet of Things (IoT) architecture. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also discusses the computational complexity of encryption algorithms and their implementation on low-powered devices, which falls under the category of cs.IT (Information Theory). The IoT architecture involves communication between devices, which can be modeled as a network, making cs.CY (Computational Geometry) another likely category. The paper also discusses the architecture of the proposed algorithm, which involves a mixture of feistel and substitution-permutation network, making cs.SY (Systems and Control) a possible category. Finally, the paper discusses the implementation of the algorithm on a low-cost micro-controller, which falls under the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning).
